The paper deals with image-to-image translation, which is a topic primarily studied in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of deep learning techniques, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces the concept of feature masks, which can be considered a form of image segmentation, a topic studied in computer graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on various datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
